Sentencas: The electrochemical oxidative regeneration method is proposed for the sulfur poisoned solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) in this study, and successfully applied to the sulfur poisoned La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCrM) anode of SOFC.
Titulo: Regeneration of sulfur poisoned La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode of solid oxide fuel cell using electrochemical oxidative method

Sentencas: Electrochemical oxidative regeneration method can transport oxygen ions to anode from cathode in inert gas at constant current, and further clear the sulfur poisoned products (S-8, MnS and La2O2S) which are produced in dry H-2 that contained 50 ppm (v) H2S contaminant, in addition, the evenly distributed MnO catalytic nanoparticles can be generated in regeneration process.
Titulo: Regeneration of sulfur poisoned La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode of solid oxide fuel cell using electrochemical oxidative method

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the SOFC with the sulfur poisoned LSCrM anode can be fully recovered in a short time (15 min), and interestingly enough, the repeated sulfur poisoning and electrochemical oxidative regeneration process do not cause a sharp deterioration in electrochemical performance of the SOFC.
Titulo: Regeneration of sulfur poisoned La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode of solid oxide fuel cell using electrochemical oxidative method

Sentencas: The sulfur poisoning and electrochemical oxidative regeneration mechanism of the SOFC with LSCrM anode are evaluated in detail.
Titulo: Regeneration of sulfur poisoned La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode of solid oxide fuel cell using electrochemical oxidative method
